<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5735] Static type checking error when calling a method with generics that receives a Class&lt;T&gt; and a T object, and the instantiation of T is a parametric type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5735</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I have the following code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@groovy.transform.CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyClass {

   &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;T&amp;gt; void someMethod (java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; clazz, T object) {}

   void method() {
      List&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; list = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
      someMethod(java.util.List.class, list)  
   }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MyClass().method()
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it throws this error &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Static type checking&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; - Cannot call MyClass#someMethod(java.lang.Class &amp;lt;T&amp;gt;, java.lang.Object &amp;lt;T&amp;gt;) with arguments &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;java.lang.Class &amp;lt;java.util.List&amp;gt;, java.util.List &amp;lt;String&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The issue here is that T is being inferred as List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;, therefore it expects to have a Class&amp;lt;List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;&amp;gt; (which cannot be constructed).&lt;br/&gt;
If instead T becomes just List, a raw type will be used in the second argument, and it should work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an additional note, this example used to work in Groovy 2.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
